cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with video object segmentation using a fully-convolutional neural network architecture, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of generic semantic information learned on ImageNet, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The task of video object segmentation involves processing and analyzing video data, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that improves the state of the art, which could be considered a contribution to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
